<br>
--------------------<br>
<br>
Absor,<br>
<br>
Because of the class tweaking going on I posted a thread on a few good mage forums to get the general consensus on what they think could be done to help our class post 50.  No mages are arguing we are powerful enough in the 1-50 game, but when it comes to 50+ on raids we aren’t always first on the list of necessities.  So here they are…<br>
<br>
Post 50 Pets:<br>
<br>
Since post 50+ pets don't progress along the same growth curve as pre-50 pets and in some areas pets are prohibited by groups, mages need some more abilities to fit into the post 50 world. COTH is good, but it is not enough, especially since it is a rare drop and level 55. Mages need some fixes along the lines of other classes. When the power of other pet classes pets was decreased, they were tweaked with the addition of new spells to compensate such as hp/mana transfer. We are not asking for a clarity here or any mana regen at all (it would be nice) since you have said it wont ever happen.  Not overpowering, but useful to groups when pets and DOT's were not of service. Mages need a similar tweak.  There are some suggestions further in the letter.<br>
<br>
Post 50th Fire Pets:<br>
<br>
The reason that these pets need to be fixed is because the post 50th spells should have, in the very least, kept the Magician's power status quo compared to lvl 1-50. By replacing our standard Fire Pet with the Wizzie Fire Pet Verant has taken away a pet that had a lot of uses in various situations and replaced it with a pet that has limited uses in very certain situations. Effectively, this has lowered the Magician's power post 50th because the variety in pet summons has actually gone down because of this. <br>
Suggestions: Make 52 and 58 fire pet non-aggressive pets, they are wizards after all…no wizard runs up to something to try and cast on it and melee it at the same time, so if this is really a wizard pet, make it stand back and cast.  Also it has been suggested to give this pet the lvl 49 fire pet DS and maybe lower its Hp’s because it will not be fighting and will die fast this wouldn’t be too overpowering if tweaked a little.<br>
<br>
Specialization:<br>
<br>
Up until Kunark it was very hard to decide on what you should specialize in because many of the good high lvl Damage spells were of both.  Since Kunark came out almost every high level DD that we get is Evocation.  We are mages, not wizards, we are Conjurers and Summoners post 50, why are we casting Evocation spells, that’s a wizards job. Please changes some of the post 50+ spells to Conjuration based.<br>
<br>
Group Damage Shields:<br>
<br>
You have taken under consideration making shaman group buffs more mana efficient.  I hope that you take Mage 50+ group damage shields under consideration for this too.  As it is, it takes less mana to cast DS on your group members than just to cast this spell.  <br>
Additional Idea: If it can not have its mana efficiency tweaked, is it possible to include pets in the casting of this spell? That would more than make up for the extra mana cost. <br>
<br>
Pets in Group Spells:<br>
<br>
Although I am not sure if it can’t or won’t be done many mages would love to see our pets and all other pets included in-group buffs and bard songs.  Not sure on exactly the specifics on if this would make our pets too strong, but maybe they would be a welcomed addition in place of a tank for once.<br>
<br>
Rain spells:<br>
<br>
Remove pets as eating a wave in Rain type spells... now that they are PC’s this may be easier than it was before to do.<br>
As is currently Rain spells are resisted a lot more often than any other DD, this grouped with pets eating a wave of it puts it in the back of many mages spell books (if they even bought it).  We are not asking for it to be on par with our other Fire and Magic based DD’s on resistances, but somewhere a little closer?<br>
<br>
New Spell Ideas:<br>
<br>
Pet Heals: 2 new pet heals... 1 at 39 ... 1 at 50 (300 at 39 with slightly better mana to hp ratio than level 20 spell.. 500 at 50 again with slightly better mana to hp ratio than 39.. or Make level 20 spell increase in effectiveness as level increases.<br>
<br>
New Summon Ideas:<br>
<br>
Shard of the Core: Great idea for a spell the +poison resistance’s are a godsend on some raids, until you realize its No Drop which makes it a very small increase in power over previous resistance dagger summons.  Was this a mistake making it no drop?  <br>
<br>
More Resistance’s Summons: They are great for raids and overall period, even if it means adding some resistance’s onto our existing 50+ summons and making them trade-able.<br>
<br>
Weapon Summons: A couple good post 1 Handed weapon summonings.   Place a level restriction on them as with some items with possible proc..(Kunark and Velious weapons should warrant a change like this.. More for CR than anything)<br>
<br>
An upgrade to Mod rod that we get at lvl 49:<br>
Modulators Rod<br>
Mana Cost 250:<br>
Takes 500 HP and gives back 350 mana <br>
Conclusion -500 HP for 100 mana.<br>
Numbers adjusted appropriately.<br>
<br>
FA Quest:<br>
<br>
Pegasus Cloak: It was said that you weren’t sure if this was No Drop or not and have since learned that it is.  This camp is one of the absolute worst in the game, if you can not increase the spawn and or drop rate of this, Please take off the no drop tag so that we can at least buy it.<br>
<br>
Staff of Elemental Mastery: Earth  - For many mages that I have talked to this is the only piece that they need to complete the FA.  Because Gods are on a week spawn rate, many mages will be stuck here for a VERY long time if not forever hoping they see a staff, let alone get one.  Please increase the drop rate on this staff as it is not something that really overpowers our pets, but is ungodly (godly?) hard to get.<br>
