Ultimate Fix for Pets not allowed in certain situations:<br>
<br>
The reason that pets aren't allowed in some situations is almost always because of pathing.  For instance, areas of Hate where the MoB can go up on the wall and a pet might take a strange path to/from the MoB, or that clearing before the castle in the Hole, etc.  <br>
<br>
The Fix: Level 50 spell called &quot;Possess Summoned&quot; (or something of that nature) which allows us to completely control our pet.   This would negate pathing and thus negate the major handicap to Magicians post-50th.  This is not something that fixes a weakness for Magicians that is there by design, its highly doubtful that Verant designed bad pathing areas on purpose just to make haveing a pet more difficult.     The spell would have the drawback of leaving the caster stationary and defenseless during this time.   There would be no set duration for the spell, but an activatable key for &quot;unposessing&quot; the pet which would act as a spell with a 3 second casting time -- Meaning if we are posessing our pet and our body is being attacked it would take 3 seconds to gain control of the body back.   <br>
<br>
This casting time to unposess essentially means we won't be posessing our pets in every day situations because it is too dangers (3 seconds is long enough to take a massive amount of damage from a MoB), but would be useful in many situations like Plane raids where, if the plane raid goes bad, the Magician is likely dead anyway.   <p> <br>
